## 8. Open Decisions Carried Over / Added

- **~~Scout clawback mechanism (Section 5, Case B)~~ — RESOLVED.** Decided policy: mistake → Client refunded, Scout still paid in full (platform absorbs the cost, matching industry-standard practice). Fraud → Client refunded, Scout payment withheld (pre-payout) or treated as an absorbed loss with no attempted clawback (post-payout, Case B) — see Sections 5 and 5a.
- **New, not yet decided: what counts as "Mistake" vs. "Fraud" needs a written guideline for admins**, even though the final call is always a human judgment. Worth drafting a short rubric (e.g. "blurry/dark/incomplete = mistake by default; under-15-second clips, static/motionless footage, or GPS far from the property = treat as likely fraud pending review") so different admins apply the distinction consistently rather than each developing their own informal sense of where the line sits.
- **New, not yet decided: fraud flag thresholds** — exact duration cutoffs, motion-variance thresholds, GPS mismatch radius, and the rolling window/count for `'RepeatOffender'` all need real values, ideally tuned using some real submission data once available rather than guessed in the abstract before any Scout has used the system.
- **New, not yet decided: does a `'WithheldFraud'` resolution automatically suspend the Scout's account, or just flag it for separate admin review?** Given the "kick him off the platform" intent behind this whole discussion, I'd lean toward: a single `'WithheldFraud'` resolution flags the account for mandatory review (not automatic suspension, since a human should still look at the specific case), but a `'RepeatOffender'` flag (2+ confirmed fraud resolutions) triggers a strong recommended-suspension prompt in the admin UI. Not yet built or confirmed as the actual policy.
- Whether `marketplace_purchases` should sync to Xero under the same account/tracking category as inspection revenue, or a distinct one for cleaner reporting — leaning toward distinct, not yet confirmed.
- `webhook_events` retention policy — how long to keep raw webhook payloads (compliance/storage consideration, not just a technical one).
- Whether a `'Failed'` `xero_sync_status` should trigger an automatic retry, an admin alert, or both — not yet decided. Given the earlier-established principle of "never silently lose a record of money movement," I'd lean toward both: an automatic retry (e.g. 3 attempts with backoff) and, if all retries fail, a visible flag somewhere in the admin portal (a new "Sync Issues" indicator, perhaps on `admin/dashboard.html`) so a human notices rather than this failing silently the way several other things did earlier in this project.
